t, from a structural point of view, passive\ngalaxies are a more heterogeneous population than star-forming systems, and may\nhave followed a variety of evolutionary paths. This also suggests that, if\ndispersion-dominated bulges still grow significantly at $z\\sim$0, this\ngenerally takes place during, or after, the quenching phase.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 11 Apr 2022 01:04:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-05-04"}
